0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Feb 09, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104njw1665702571289.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/njw1665702571289.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/njw1665702571289.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"njw1665702571289\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify the file extensions that are treated as text files, rather than binary files.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"njw1665702571289__topic_d143360e1_d143361e1_d143362e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"njw1665702571289__p_d143363e1_d143364e1_d143365e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS</span> { <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code> } <var class=\"keyword varname\">ExtensionsList</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"njw1665702571289__section_ygl_pjm_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d274455e65\">Arguments</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"njw1665702571289__p_d143369e1_d143370e1_d143371e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">ExtensionsList</var>—list of files\n            extensions that are considered to be text files rather than binary files. If set with no\n            list, all files are treated as binary files.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"njw1665702571289__section_yjt_qjm_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d274455e76\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"njw1665702571289__table_d17297e1_d17298e1_d17299e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Application</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">.xml;.trx;.asn;.txt;.htm;.hts;.html</code>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"njw1665702571289__section_pnv_5jm_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d274455e124\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"njw1665702571289__p_d143378e1_d143379e1_d143380e1\">The setting allows the user to determine which file\n            extensions are considered text and which are considered binary.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"njw1665702571289__p_d143381e1_d143382e1_d143383e1\">When <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">filemove</span>,\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lfilemove</span>, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">filecopy</span>, and\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lfilecopy</span> transport files to or from zip archives, or across\n            operating systems or media, Uniface handles text files differently than binary files. It\n            copies binary files as-is, but it automatically adjusts text file attributes so that EOL\n            characters and optional character set conversions match the platform. This may result in\n            changes in the file size, making it appear that source and target files are not the\n            same.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"njw1665702571289__p_d143384e1_d143385e1_d143386e1\">By default, Uniface treats files as text files if\n            they have the text file attribute in zip files, or if they have one of the following\n            extensions: <span class=\"ph filepath\">.xml</span>, <span class=\"ph filepath\">.trx</span>,\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">.asn</span>, <span class=\"ph filepath\">.txt</span>, <span class=\"ph filepath\">.htm</span>,\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">.hts</span>, <span class=\"ph filepath\">.html</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"njw1665702571289__p_d143387e1_d143388e1_d143389e1\">You can use the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS</span> setting to determine how these Uniface\n            commands handle specific types of files. If you want to switch off automatic\n            cross-platform text attribute handling, set <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS</span> to\n            an empty string.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"njw1665702571289__section_l1q_xjm_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d274455e182\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">$TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS =</code></h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"njw1665702571289__p_d143393e1_d143394e1_d143395e1\">Turn off automatic text attribute handling in\n            ProcScript commands for copying and moving files:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"njw1665702571289__pre_p2z_xjm_lwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS =</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"njw1665702571289__p_d143396e1_d143397e1_d143398e1\">Restrict automatic text attribute handling to\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">.xml</span> and <span class=\"ph filepath\">.txt</span> files:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"njw1665702571289__pre_ydz_xjm_lwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS = .xml;.txt</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530285\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530285\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Feb 09, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Specify the file extensions that are treated as text files, rather than binary files. $TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS { = } ExtensionsList Arguments ExtensionsList —list of files extensions that are considered to be text files rather than binary files. If set with no list, all files are treated as binary files. Defaults Assignment file: Application Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: .xml;.trx;.asn;.txt;.htm;.hts;.html Description The setting allows the user to determine which file extensions are considered text and which are considered binary. When filemove , lfilemove , filecopy , and lfilecopy transport files to or from zip archives, or across operating systems or media, Uniface handles text files differently than binary files. It copies binary files as-is, but it automatically adjusts text file attributes so that EOL characters and optional character set conversions match the platform. This may result in changes in the file size, making it appear that source and target files are not the same. By default, Uniface treats files as text files if they have the text file attribute in zip files, or if they have one of the following extensions: .xml , .trx , .asn , .txt , .htm , .hts , .html . You can use the $TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS setting to determine how these Uniface commands handle specific types of files. If you want to switch off automatic cross-platform text attribute handling, set $TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS to an empty string. Example: $TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS = Turn off automatic text attribute handling in ProcScript commands for copying and moving files: $TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS = Copy Restrict automatic text attribute handling to .xml and .txt files: $TEXT_FILE_EXTENSIONS = .xml;.txt Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}